===============================================
Standard .gitignore for CMake Projects
===============================================
----------------
1. CMake Build and Cache Files
----------------
Ignore the primary build directory, typically named 'build' or 'bin'.
If you use an alternative name (like 'out' or 'Release'), you should add it here.
build/
Build/
bin/
out/
debug/
release/
Release/
Debug/

Ignore the CMake cache and manifest files
CMakeCache.txt
CMakeFiles/
Makefile
cmake_install.cmake
install_manifest.txt

Do not ignore the following files, as they are essential for other
developers to configure their build environment.
!CMakeLists.txt
!*/CMakeLists.txt

----------------
2. Executables and Object Files
----------------
Ignore compiled object files and dependency files
*.o
*.d
*.obj
*.rsp

Ignore static and shared libraries
*.lib
*.a
*.so
*.dylib
*.dll

Ignore common executable formats
*.exe
*.out
*.app
*.obj
*.elf

----------------
3. Editor/IDE Specific Files
----------------
Visual Studio / VS Code
.vs/
.vscode/

CLion
.idea/

Xcode
*.xcodeproj/
*.xcworkspace/
DerivedData/

----------------
4. Operating System Generated Files
----------------
macOS
.DS_Store

Windows
Thumbs.db